### Test validate-email route

### 1. Check if email exists (should return exists: true if user already registered)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/validate-email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "existing@example.com"
}

### 2. Check if email is available (should return exists: false)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/validate-email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "newuser@example.com"
}

### 3. Test invalid email format (should return 400 error)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/validate-email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "invalid-email"
}

### 4. Test missing email field (should return 400 error)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/validate-email
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### 5. Test empty email (should return 400 error)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/validate-email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": ""
}
